
Overview of adv lazily

The adv lazily has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) lazily -- (in a slow and lazy manner; "I watched the blue smoke drift lazily away on the still air")
2. idly, lazily -- (in an idle manner; "this is what I always imagined myself doing in the south of France, sitting idly, drinking coffee, watching the people")
